<div class="room-body">
<h2 class="room-title">Fluid Terrain</h2>
<p class="room-desc">A porous gabion landscape built from recycled concrete that slows floodwater and supports seasonal habitation along the creek edge. Elevated structures and terraced ground adapt to shifting water levels across flood and drought cycles.</p>
<div class="dmeta">
<div class="drow"><span class="dk">Period</span><span>2026 Spring · Columbia GSAPP</span></div>
<div class="drow"><span class="dk">Location</span><span>Santa Paula Creek, Ventura County, CA</span></div>
<div class="drow"><span class="dk">Program</span><span>Hydrological landscape infrastructure</span></div>
<div class="drow"><span class="dk">Credits</span><span>Individual · Instructor Marc Tsurumaki</span></div>
</div>
